@Node "HIS" "History"

@{b}@{u}History@{uu}@{ub}

   1.0  - First release.

   1.1  - Now the first line in the @{"configuration file" link "COF"} specifies the
          title of the selection list. It will appear on the @{"main" link "MAW"}
          @{"window" link "MAW"}'s title bar.
        - Now the script file names in the @{"configuration file" link "COF"} may be
          indented to avoid confusion with the item labels.
        - Now you can enter blank lines in the @{"configuration file" link "COF"} to
          separate the items in the selection list.
        - Added the 'MENUFILE', 'XPOS', 'YPOS', 'WIDTH' and 'HEIGHT'
          @{"ToolTypes and CLI arguments" link "TCA"}.
        - Added the sizing and zoom gadgets to the @{"main window" link "MAW"}.
        - Added the 'Project' @{"menu" link "MEN"} containing the 'Snapshot',
          'About...' and 'Quit' items.
        - Some other minor changes.

   1.2  - The program did not work on 68000/68010 machines.
        - Renamed the 'MENUFILE' @{"ToolType and CLI argument" link "TCA"} as
          'CONFIGFILE'.
        - Substituted the 'Quit' button with the 'Iconify' button (see
          @{"The main window" link "MAW"}).
        - Now the 'Snapshot' item in the 'Project' @{"menu" link "MEN"} is no longer
          available if the program is started from Shell.
        - Now the program uses the dos.library ReadArgs() function to read
          the @{"CLI arguments" link "TCA"}.
        - Doubled the number of items the selection list can hold.
        - Now you can put the @{"configuration file" link "COF"} in any directory of
          your choice. Use the 'CONFIGFILE' @{"ToolType or CLI argument" link "TCA"} to
          specify its full path name.
        - Now it is no longer necessary for you to create external script
          files. In fact, you can enter the command lines directly in the
          @{"configuration file" link "COF"}.
        - Now the selection list can contain 'sham' items (see
          @{"Configuration file" link "COF"}).
        - Now the blank lines in the @{"configuration file" link "COF"} are ignored. To
          separate the items in the selection list, use empty 'sham' items
          instead.
        - Now you can enter comments in the @{"configuration file" link "COF"}.
        - Now the scripts can be executed with a simple double-click.
        - Added the 'SCRIPTSPATH', 'STARTICONIFIED', 'EDITOR', 'BACKGROUND',
          'SHOWOUTPUT' and 'OUTPUTWINDOW' @{"ToolTypes and CLI arguments" link "TCA"}.
        - Added the 'Execute', 'Editor...', 'Window state...' and 'Iconify'
          items to the 'Project' @{"menu" link "MEN"}.
        - Added the 'Options' @{"menu" link "MEN"} containing the 'Execute in
          background' and 'Show output' items.
        - Some other minor changes.

   1.21 - If a patch like VisualPrefs or UrouHack was running, there were
          problems when resizing the @{"main window" link "MAW"} or quitting the
          program.
        - Some other minor changes.


@Endnode
